      "question": "The 4th term of an AP is 14 and the 12th term is 70. What is the first term $a$?",
      "answer": "(A)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Use the formula $a_n = a + (n-1)d$",
          "Set up two equations: $a + 3d = 14$ and $a + 11d = 70$",
          "Subtract the equations to find $d = 7$",
          "Substitute $d$ to find $a$"
        ],
        "derivation": "a + 3d = 14 \\\\ a + 11d = 70 \\\\ (a + 11d) - (a + 3d) = 70 - 14 \\\\ 8d = 56 \\implies d = 7 \\\\ a + 3(7) = 14 \\implies a = 14 - 21 = -7"
      },
